OL,5, Lesley Lokko has become the first      
OL,6, African woman to be awarded the Royal  
OL,7, Gold Medal for Architecture, for her   
OL,8, work to "democratise" the industry.    
OL,10,FThe honour is given by the Royal       
OL,11,FInstitute of British Architects (Riba) 
OL,12,Fand approved by the monarch each year. 
OL,14,FGhanaian-Scottish Lokko was also made  
OL,15,Fan OBE in the recent New Year Honours  
OL,16,Flist by King Charles, who is known to  
OL,17,Fhave a keen interest in architecture.  
OL,19,FRiba commended Lokko's work focusing on
OL,20,FAfrica and the so-called Global South. 
